# Licensed vendor data (Capital IQ exports + anything derived from them) MUST
# NOT be committed — it is proprietary S&P data the user holds under license,
# and committing it to git would be redistribution. Only the pipeline code,
# the column-alias map, the manifest template, and this .gitignore are tracked.
#
# Drop your Capital IQ Screening exports here and run:
#   .venv/bin/python scripts/ingest_deal_library_exports.py \
#       --in data/vendor/deal_library --source-system "Capital IQ"
*.xls
*.xlsx
*.csv
*.json
# ...but keep the tracked scaffolding:
!column_aliases.py
!source_manifests/
source_manifests/*.csv
!source_manifests/capiq_export_manifest.template.csv
!README.md
